situation: It is finals week at my college and  I am very anxious about it.

final_result.label: normal
final_result.response: I hear you, and it can be really tough to make decisions when you're feeling overwhelmed. One approach could be to break things down into smaller steps. For example, you might try listing out your subjects and prioritizing which ones you feel need the most attention. Or you could set a timer for short study sessions followed by breaks. Would either of those ideas resonate with you?
